									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.asgard.chapter.5.content",
									"fallback": "With my administrator access still active, I designed a system to limit the damage of what Voss created. I named this interface 'the Terminal'."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.asgard.chapter.5.content2",
									"fallback": "It appears after each war, allowing the winner to make a wish - the Ragnarök. By including the twenty-word limitation, I hope to restrict the damage a player could cause."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.asgard.chapter.5.content3",
									"fallback": "I have scoured every corner of Yggdrasil, studying its peoples and their cultures to hide clues there."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.asgard.chapter.5.content4",
									"fallback": "These messages are designed to only make sense to someone who already knows the outside world - players will understand, but the developers who are monitoring will only see mythological references."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.asgard.chapter.5.content5",
									"fallback": "This coded language will allow future 'gods' to gradually discover the truth about this world and, perhaps, find a way to save it."
